From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Bjarni Coenen <bjarni@coenen.dev>
Date: Mon, 7 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] serial: amba-pl011: RPi downstream fixes for RP1 serial
 reliability

Cherry-picked fixes from the RPi/RevPi downstream kernel
(revolutionpi/linux devel/revpi-6.18) to improve PL011 UART
reliability on RPi5/RP1-based platforms:

- Insert mb() after DR write for correct FIFO ordering (Phil Elwell)
- Avoid rare write-when-full error on last TX char (Phil Elwell)
- Add DMA dst_addr_width for RX slave config (Phil Elwell)
- Cap DMA RX burst to controller max capability (Phil Elwell)
- Add cts-event-workaround DT property for AMBA probe (Phil Elwell)

Upstream commits from revolutionpi/linux:
  806a1f4eaac5 ("amba_pl011: Insert mb() for correct FIFO handling")
  a8a248388de0 ("tty: amba-pl011: Avoid rare write-when-full error")
  091e870a71f7 ("serial: pl011: Request a memory width of 1 byte")
  9c6dd5502ad1 ("serial: pl011: rp1 uart support") [DMA burst subset]
  6cd2328100e1 ("amba_pl011: Add cts-event-workaround DT property")

Signed-off-by: Bjarni Coenen <bjarni@coenen.dev>
---
 drivers/tty/serial/amba-pl011.c | 24 +++++++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 23 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/tty/serial/amba-pl011.c b/drivers/tty/serial/amba-pl011.c
--- a/drivers/tty/serial/amba-pl011.c
+++ b/drivers/tty/serial/amba-pl011.c
@@ -473,6 +473,7 @@
 		struct dma_slave_config rx_conf = {
 			.src_addr = uap->port.mapbase +
 				pl011_reg_to_offset(uap, REG_DR),
 			.src_addr_width = DMA_SLAVE_BUSWIDTH_1_BYTE,
+			.dst_addr_width = DMA_SLAVE_BUSWIDTH_1_BYTE,
 			.direction = DMA_DEV_TO_MEM,
 			.src_maxburst = uap->fifosize >> 2,
 			.device_fc = false,
@@ -493,6 +494,12 @@
 				dev_info(uap->port.dev,
 					 "RX DMA disabled - no residue processing\n");
 				return;
 			}
+			/*
+			 * DMA controllers with smaller burst capabilities than 1/4
+			 * the FIFO depth will leave more bytes than expected in the
+			 * RX FIFO if mismatched.
+			 */
+			rx_conf.src_maxburst = min(caps.max_burst, rx_conf.src_maxburst);
 		}
 
 		dmaengine_slave_config(chan, &rx_conf);
@@ -1497,6 +1504,7 @@
 		return false; /* unable to transmit character */
 
 	pl011_write(c, uap, REG_DR);
+	mb();
 	uap->port.icount.tx++;
 
 	return true;
@@ -1528,6 +1536,10 @@
 		if (likely(from_irq) && count-- == 0)
 			break;
 
+		if (likely(from_irq) && count == 0 &&
+		    pl011_read(uap, REG_FR) & UART01x_FR_TXFF)
+			break;
+
 		if (!kfifo_peek(&tport->xmit_fifo, &c))
 			break;
 
@@ -2950,6 +2962,11 @@
 	if (IS_ERR(uap->clk))
 		return PTR_ERR(uap->clk);
 
+	if (of_property_read_bool(dev->dev.of_node, "cts-event-workaround")) {
+		vendor->cts_event_workaround = true;
+		dev_info(&dev->dev, "cts_event_workaround enabled\n");
+	}
+
 	uap->reg_offset = vendor->reg_offset;
 	uap->vendor = vendor;
 	uap->fifosize = vendor->get_fifosize(dev);
-- 
